<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued March 30 at 8:32AM CDT until March 30 at 9:00AM CDT by NWS Shreveport</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 900 AM CDT
FOR WESTERN MARION...SOUTH CENTRAL CASS AND NORTHWESTERN HARRISON
COUNTIES...
At 831 AM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from near Linden to Harleton, moving northeast at 35 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Linden, Berea, Harleton, Fairview, Avinger, Lassater, Pruett and Red
Hill.
TORNADO...POSSIBLE
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...&lt;.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 100 PM CDT for northeastern
Texas.
For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
